<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38072c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38072c">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38072c"> 72(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="green">[sisting]</font> at / counting noses / private member / committee of 5</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Letters to the Editor / The Size of the Commons / Members and Their Electors</b> <br>Sir,&mdash;Last night between 300 and 400 members spent the night in the House of Commons sleepless and restless.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> There was no necessity for the dilatory <mark>process of counting noses</mark>. All knew approximately how many and what kind of noses were there.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Every business man knows that <mark>a committee exceeding five in number cannot do business</mark>.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The occupation of a <mark>private member</mark> is worse than useless. <small> <a name="TT31may30" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TT31may30"><cite title="source">The Times</cite></a> (31 May 1930) 8/1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
